  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2015-03-12T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Utility Energy Service Contracts Improvement Act of 2015 \n\n This bill amends the National Energy Conservation Policy Act to make explicit that utility energy service contracts (UESCs) may have a contract period of up to 25 years. UESCs are contracts that allow utilities to provide federal agencies with energy and water efficiency improvements and demand reduction services.\n\nUESC conditions must include requirements for measurement, verification, and performance assurances or guarantees of the savings."
  }, 
